SIMPLE: sallow
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sallow
<hw>Sal"low</hw> <pr>(s⟦acr⟧l"l⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>salwe</ets>, AS. <ets>sealh</ets>; akin to OHG. <ets>salaha</ets>,
G. <ets>salweide</ets>, Icel. <ets>selja</ets>, L. <ets>salix</ets>, Ir.
<ets>sail</ets>, <ets>saileach</ets>, Gael. <ets>seileach</ets>, W.
<ets>helyg</ets>, Gr. <grk>"eli`kh</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
willow; willow twigs.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And bend the pliant <qex>sallow</qex> to a shield.</q>
<rj><qau>Fawkes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>sallow</qex> knows the basketmaker's thumb.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name given to certain species of
willow, especially those which do not have flexible shoots, as
<spn>Salix caprea</spn>, <spn>Salix cinerea</spn>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sallow thorn</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a European
thorny shrub (<spn>Hippophae rhamnoides</spn>) much like an Elaeagnus.
The yellow berries are sometimes used for making jelly, and the plant
affords a yellow dye.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sallow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sallow
<hw>Sal"low</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Sallower</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sallowest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>salu</ets>; akin to D.
<ets>zaluw</ets>, OHG. <ets>salo</ets>, Icel. <ets>s⟦oum⟧lr</ets>
yellow.]</ety> <def>Having a yellowish color; of a pale, sickly color,
tinged with yellow; <as>as, a <ex>sallow</ex> skin</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sallow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sallow
<hw>Sal"low</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To tinge with sallowness.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>July breathes hot, <qex>sallows</qex> the crispy fields.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sallowish</ent>⟦br⟧
